         <abstract>
            <p>Linear programming and integer programming are both concerned with maximizing shareholder wealth solely in terms of financial constraints. This paper gives an illustration of goal programming applied to capital budgeting, which incorporates directly the existence of multiple conflicting goals.</p>
         </abstract>
